wfDsuCsuIfEntry.name: wfDsuCsuIfEntry
wfDsuCsuIfEntry.description: An entry in the DSU CSU IF table

wfDsuCsuIfSlot.name: wfDsuCsuIfSlot
wfDsuCsuIfSlot.description: Instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfDsuCsuIfConnector.name: wfDsuCsuIfConnector
wfDsuCsuIfConnector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by the driver.

wfDsuCsuSoftRev.name: wfDsuCsuSoftRev
wfDsuCsuSoftRev.description: Displays the Software Revision of the DSU CSU card.

wfDsuCsuHardRev.name: wfDsuCsuHardRev
wfDsuCsuHardRev.description: Displays the Hardware Revision of the DSU CSU card.

wfDsuCsuOpMode.name: wfDsuCsuOpMode
wfDsuCsuOpMode.description: Identifies the type of telco service that the DSU CSU is connected to. Opmode should be set to dds1-56kbps (1) when connected to a DDS1 56 Kbps line. Opmode should be set to cc-64kbps (2) when connected to a Clear Channel 64Kbps line.

wfDsuCsuTxClkSelect.name: wfDsuCsuTxClkSelect
wfDsuCsuTxClkSelect.description: Default timing, or clock, source for transmiting data to the network. There must be only one source on a DDS line. Timing should always be slave (1) when connected to a network. Timing should be set to master (2) on either end of a private-wire configuration, with the other end being set to slave (1).

wfDsuCsuUnitReset.name: wfDsuCsuUnitReset
wfDsuCsuUnitReset.description: Enables the operator to remotely reset the unit. Using this command will cause the unit to terminate all its connections and drop data.

wfDsuCsu64KTxMonitor.name: wfDsuCsu64KTxMonitor
wfDsuCsu64KTxMonitor.description: This signal is used in 64K Clear Channel mode to suppress customer data in the event that the data duplicates a network control code. A setting of enabled(1) suppresses customer data. A setting of disabled(2) allows all customer data through, which could potentially put the other end into a loop if the data duplicates a network control code.

wfDsuCsuOpState.name: wfDsuCsuOpState
wfDsuCsuOpState.description: Indicates the current operating state of the DSU CSU card.

wfDsuCsuServiceStatus.name: wfDsuCsuServiceStatus
wfDsuCsuServiceStatus.description: The Current status of the physical interface. Your network carrier can send Out-of-Service or Maintenance Mode codes.

wfDsuCsuV54Lpbk.name: wfDsuCsuV54Lpbk
wfDsuCsuV54Lpbk.description: Enables the operator to control, and examine the state of, V.54 loopbacks within the DSU CSU.

wfDsuCsuV54Timer.name: wfDsuCsuV54Timer
wfDsuCsuV54Timer.description: Duration in seconds that a test specified in wfDsuCsuTestLpbk is to execute.

wfDsuCsuV54Errors.name: wfDsuCsuV54Errors
wfDsuCsuV54Errors.description: Indicates the number of errors reported during the last loopback test. This count will only be updated for loopbacks with test pattern.

wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow.name: wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow
wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow.description: Indicates the number of minutes within the window in which the availability of the line (network) is to be calculated. The availability of the line is an indication of the percentage of time the line has been in service. It is calculated as follows: (((wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow*60) - (wfDsuCsuCqmsLaErrCnt*wfDsuCsuCqmsLaPollRate))/ wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow*60)

wfDsuCsuCqmsLaErrors.name: wfDsuCsuCqmsLaErrors
wfDsuCsuCqmsLaErrors.description: Indicates the total number of seconds that the line was not in service in the last window of size wfDsuCsuCqmsLaWindow.

wfDsuCsuCqmsLaPollRate.name: wfDsuCsuCqmsLaPollRate
wfDsuCsuCqmsLaPollRate.description: Indicates the number of seconds between polls for line status from the DsuCsu. A value of 1 forces polling every second. A value of 60 forces polling every minute.

wfDsuCsuCqmsReset.name: wfDsuCsuCqmsReset
wfDsuCsuCqmsReset.description: Resets the CQMS counters to their default values. For Line Availability, wfDsuCsuCqmsLaErrCnt is reset.

wfDsuCsuOOSErrors.name: wfDsuCsuOOSErrors
wfDsuCsuOOSErrors.description: The number of seconds in which Out of Service control codes were received from the Telco. The counter is incremented whenever a sample within a second indicated the unit received an out of service control code.

wfDsuCsuFrameErrors.name: wfDsuCsuFrameErrors
wfDsuCsuFrameErrors.description: The number of seconds in which the unit was out of frame with the Telco. This is only applicable in 64K mode. The counter is incremented whenever a sample within a second indicated the unit was out of frame.

wfDsuCsuLOLErrors.name: wfDsuCsuLOLErrors
wfDsuCsuLOLErrors.description: The number of seconds in which the unit has detected that no signal is present on the line, and/or no line is present.

wfDsuCsuInitState.name: wfDsuCsuInitState
wfDsuCsuInitState.description: Indictes the state of the DSU/CSU initialization sequence. The state will indicate if the DSU/CSU has been initialized and is in the *monitor* state polling the card for line condition, or in the *loopback state running a user-initiated loopback

wfDsuCsuIfTrap.name: wfDsuCsuIfTrap
wfDsuCsuIfTrap.description: Indicates a change in the status of the line. The value returned in the trap will indicate the current state as defined in wfDsuCsuServiceStatus.
